The existing microbenchmarks are not widely known
and are not used to drive design / coding decissions. At the same time those test add to the maintanance cost:
- use hand-written instructions;
- plug into runtime internals and are fragile;
- require development of mocks for the runtime internals.

Those tests are removed since they are costly to maintain and, at the same, don't provide enough value.

